I was a bit sleepy when I wrote the comment above. Please consider the following function as an example of what I&#x27;m talking about, instead of the confused &quot;chevron&quot; function above. This is make-believe C:<p><pre><code>  MaybeInt bind (MaybeInt a, (function : int -> MaybeInt a) f)
  {
    if (a.maybe_value == JUST)
      f(a.integer);
    else
      nothing();
  }

  MaybeInt chevron (MaybeInt a, MaybeInt b)
  {
    bind(a, lambda(x){ b });
  }
</code></pre>
/* Just 5 >>= (\x -> Just $ x + 1) */
bind( just(5), lambda(x){ just(x+1); } );

From the exploit code:<p><pre><code>    memset(&serv_addr, &#x27;0&#x27;, sizeof(serv_addr));
